candidates.title: Make CTRL+C finally work in the web and minor tweaks
Add support to interrupt execution via CTRL+C
Parameterize the exec URL of the REPL
candidates.body:
This modifies the SHARE command so that the exec URL for public scripts
is configurable.  The cli always passes a fixed value, but this allows
the web UI to properly display its own origin.

candidates.title: Add new client crate and parameterize service URL
Release EndBASIC 0.8.1
candidates.body:
Minor release to ship a couple of important usability fixes and to
migrate away from Google Analytics.

candidates.title: Post-release version bump and build fixes
Release EndBASIC 0.8.0
candidates.body:
As part of this change, tweak the release process slightly and update
the front page notes to highlight the new features.

candidates.title: Misc improvements for the web UI
Reimplement the web UI using a custom canvas
Extend CLEAR and NEW to reset machine state
Fix and test the SDL console
Miscellaneous prework to support cloud drives
candidates.body: My local branch is going too big and hard to manage, so start merging some of the preliminary work to support cloud drives.

candidates.title: Add support for the EndBASIC cloud service
Add basic GPIO support for the Raspberry Pi
Big reorganization
candidates.body: Make the REPL be part of `cli`, reuse that for the `web`, reshuffle integration tests, and move the standard library to a new `std` crate.
